description:
Songsterr accepts .gp files now, so maybe I'll take the 8-string!
Will revert if not

- Fixed and rewrote drums :D
- Fixed rhythm guitar in the bridge :v
- Added more P.M. in all guitars :P
- Minor correction in bars 53, 61, 103, 111, 137, 145, and 153 for lead and harmony guitars :|
- Minor fixes in rhythm guitar and bass :3

- Removed 4-string bass
- Updated personnel
- Rewrote guitar notation and fixed some errors.

Revised old tab according to sourced video (Thanks for linking that!)

- Added Vocals
- Added names
- Sherwood says he plays a 5-string, but I kept the 4-string in just in case

Reversing recent changes as they were in the wrong tuning, as seen by Kevin Sherwood's own video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DyVHLo4e7Xw

- Rewrote bass track
- Updated section names
- Added a vocal placeholder track

Gp5 doesn't like 8 string guitars, so I had to split it into two.
Also, 6-string arrangement.
Fixed a part in the last chorus where the last harmony started too early.
Fixed the harmony in the last chorus. The guitar is supposed to be in a different tuning but it wasn't, so the harmony wasn't humanly playable without a capo.
I did fixed dissonance in a lead part, made half the palm mutes too. it's so much that i just don't have the attention span to do it fully lol
